A LOOOONG time ago, back when Ceehaz still drew exclusively oni and monstergirls, he created the Dog Knights. They were initially very individually-defined, yet still effectively operated as a traveling group of different RPG classes in waifur form. No greater internal plot, just a bunch of cute anthros out questing and looting. One day, in response to a question, Cee elaborated on the girls' partner preferences, and Jeane was stated to being something of a free spirit; or bi in essence. It wasn't long after when he began drawing her taking more directed interest with Rory, the Doberman, and that's around the time the only girls besides these two became relegated to "mass comic relief" while essentially the entire loose plot of their ongoing journey reframed itself around Jeane and Rory being the mooching/cold-shoulder lesbian main characters. And that's... basically evolved into their entire character since day one. Jeane used to be depicted as having a deeper connection with nature, and she's since been severely flanderized into acting like an obsessive, unrequited and dumb turbo gash smasher with no off-switch. It's fine to make her the main appeal, because hey, boobs and muscles and feetpaws are hot, but this is the most blatant character assassination I've ever seen from a furry artist.
